# Continuation and Handoff Rule

- Start every new session by reading `docs/PHASE_LOG.md`, `README.md`, `api/README.md`, and `front-end/README.md`.
- Identify the latest pushed commit before making changes and continue from the next planned increment.
- Keep phase scope strict: do not jump ahead unless explicitly requested.
- Update `docs/PHASE_LOG.md` for each increment with status, done scope, and verification results.
- Prefer small, phase-scoped commits with clear why-focused messages.
- Never amend old commits unless explicitly requested.
- Never force-push.
- Keep terminals clean: avoid leaving interactive or hanging processes.
- Run verification before closing an increment and report exact pass/fail outcomes.
- If verification fails, fix blockers first; do not mark increment done until checks pass.
- Frontend verification order should be explicit: `install -> typecheck -> lint -> unit tests -> e2e`.
- Keep unit tests and Playwright E2E isolated; do not run Playwright specs via Bun unit test command.
- After dependency upgrades, expect compatibility follow-up (TS config, lint/plugin changes, API/type updates) before closing increment.
- Do not leave strict lint rules disabled without tracking: log rationale and add a dedicated cleanup increment to re-enable.
- If Bun is unavailable in tool runtime, use a Bun container fallback and report that verification context clearly.
- Split dependency refresh commits from feature commits unless user explicitly asks to bundle them.
